Borno State Governor, Kashim Shettima, along with some National Assembly members yesterday paid visits and held separate closed-door meetings with the Minister of Defence, Mansur Dan- Ali; the Chief of Army Staff, Lieutenant-General Tukur Buratai and Director-General, State Security Services, Yusuf Magaji Bichi, over security matters in Borno State. The three meetings were at the instance of Shettima. The meetings discussed issues of security, including the recent relocation of residents in Jakana, a town in Konduga Local Government Area, to an IDP camp in Maiduguri, which the military in Borno State said was for operational purpose in the ongoing fight against Boko Haram. Shettima was accompanied by chairmen of the Senate and House of Representatives committees on Defence, Senator Abubakar Kyari and Hon. Betara Aliyu, respectively, the Chairman, Senate Committee on Rules and Business, Senator Baba Kaka Bashir Garbai and two House of Representativesâ€™ members-elect. The governor and his delegation first met with the DG, SSS at the service headquarters about 1.30p.m. before meeting the Defence Minister at a private residence at about 4p.m. after which the delegation was at the Army Headquarters at 5p.m. for another meeting with the Chief of Army Staff for more than one hour. All the meetings were held behind closed-doors in Abuja.